statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from "conversations" where "conversations"."user_id" = 1 and "conversations"."user_id" is not null
select count(*) as aggregate from "messages" where exists (select * from "conversations" where "messages"."conversation_id" = "conversations"."id" and "user_id" = 1)
select count(*) as aggregate from "conversations" where "conversations"."user_id" = 1 and "conversations"."user_id" is not null and "status" = 'active'
select count(*) as aggregate from "conversations" where "conversations"."user_id" = 1 and "conversations"."user_id" is not null and "status" = 'completed'

select DATE(created_at) as date, COUNT(*) as count from "messages" where exists (select * from "conversations" where "messages"."conversation_id" = "conversations"."id" and "user_id" = 1) and "created_at" >= '2026-01-17 17:16:10' group by "date" order by "date" asc

select "persona_id", COUNT(*) as message_count from "messages" where exists (select * from "conversations" where "messages"."conversation_id" = "conversations"."id" and "user_id" = 1) and "persona_id" is not null group by "persona_id" order by "message_count" desc limit 10
